---
// WhatsApp Messaging Policy Page — public, unauthenticated.
// Documents the WhatsApp opt-in flow, consent language and disclosures.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="WhatsApp Messaging Policy"
  description="How DriveSchoolPro WhatsApp notifications work — pupils opt in to transactional lesson reminders, booking confirmations and payment receipts from their instructor. Reply STOP to opt out or HELP for help."
>
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="bg-gray-100 py-3">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'WhatsApp Messaging Policy' }
      ]} />
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">WhatsApp Messaging Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: 27 June 2026</p>
        <div class="prose max-w-none">

<p>This page explains how WhatsApp notifications work on DriveSchoolPro, how pupils opt in, what they receive, and how to opt out. DriveSchoolPro is operated by <strong>LEAVE.REVIEW LTD</strong> (company number 05408918), registered in England and Wales.</p>

<p><em>WhatsApp reminders are rolling out. Until WhatsApp is enabled for your instructor, lesson reminders are sent by email.</em></p>

<h2>Who sends and receives messages</h2>

<p>Messages are sent by a pupil's own driving instructor through the DriveSchoolPro platform, to pupils who hold an account with that instructor. All messages are transactional and relate to the pupil's own driving lessons. DriveSchoolPro does not send marketing or promotional messages.</p>

<h2>How you opt in</h2>

<p>When a pupil adds their mobile number in DriveSchoolPro, they are shown a consent checkbox and must actively opt in before any WhatsApp message is sent. The wording the pupil sees is:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-5">
  <p class="flex gap-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
    <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 font-semibold text-brand-navy" aria-hidden="true">&#9745;</span>
    <span>&ldquo;I agree to receive WhatsApp notifications from DriveSchoolPro about my driving lessons (reminders, booking confirmations, cancellations, and payment receipts). Reply STOP to opt out, HELP for help. See the Privacy Policy and Terms.&rdquo;</span>
  </p>
</div>

<p>Consent is never pre-ticked and is never a condition of using DriveSchoolPro. A pupil who does not opt in simply does not receive WhatsApp notifications — they can still receive lesson reminders by email.</p>

<h2>What messages you'll receive</h2>

<p>After opting in, a pupil may receive transactional messages about their own lessons, including:</p>

<ul>
<li>Lesson reminders</li>
<li>Booking confirmations</li>
<li>Reschedule and cancellation alerts</li>
<li>Payment receipts</li>
<li>Account notifications</li>
</ul>

<h2>Message frequency</h2>

<p>Message frequency varies depending on the pupil's lesson schedule.</p>

<h2>Opting out and getting help</h2>

<p>Reply <strong>STOP</strong> at any time to opt out of WhatsApp notifications. Reply <strong>HELP</strong> for assistance. Pupils can also contact <a href="mailto:support@driveschoolpro.com">support@driveschoolpro.com</a> for help, or manage their notification preferences from within their DriveSchoolPro account.</p>

<h2>How we handle your data</h2>

<p>Mobile numbers are used only to send the pupil transactional messages about their own lessons. We do not share, sell, or rent mobile numbers or messaging opt-in consent to any third parties or affiliates for their own marketing or promotional purposes. WhatsApp messages are delivered via the WhatsApp Business Platform (Meta). For full details of how we handle personal data, see our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

<h2>Related policies</h2>

<p>This WhatsApp Messaging Policy should be read alongside our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/terms/">Terms of Service</a>.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
